# Code book
#This code book shows seevral steps for performing the operations scripted in run_analysis.R

1. Call the library `read.table` and 'plyr'
* The required data for this project is downlaoded from(https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/getdata%2Fprojectfiles%2FUCI%20HAR%20Dataset.zip)
2.Load feature data set `features.txt` 
3.Loads and appends train dataset using `X_train.txt`, `y_train.txt`, `subject_train.txt`
4.Loads and appends test dataset using `X_test.txt`, `y_test.txt`, `subject_test.txt`
5. Appends train and test data
6. Rearrange the data using id
7. Loading activity labels `activity_labels.txt`
8. Changes the data activity row to use the activity labels
9. Extracts the `mean`,`std` into dataset1
10. Saves dataset1 into `result/dataset1.csv`
11. Uses plur to calculate mean on activity for each id
12. Appends `_mean` to all data columns
13. The the tidy data set using 'write.table' command


#***Additional information
#dataset1.csv
##contains 10299 rows and 81 columns in a default csv format.

#dataset2.csv
##contains 180 rows and 81 columns in a default csv format.

